Basal metabolic rate, fat ratio and muscle mass can affect the body age

A little health tip: stick to daily exercise, eat a reasonable diet and keep a good mood, you will find that your body will be younger and younger through day-to-day accumulation. Your weight is on the high side, being strong and obese.

Body age is calculated on the basis of basal metabolic rate. People of the same weight have different proportions of body composition and different ages. People with more muscle mass and a higher basal metabolic rate tend to have a younger body and vice versa.
BMI is a better indicator of a person\'s level of obesity than their weight.

BMI is calculated by dividing weight in kilograms by height in meters squared. BMI is a measure commonly used internationally to assess obesity. BMI is more accurate than weight in measuring the body\'s risk of heart disease, high blood pressure and other conditions associated with being overweight.
You are a little bit fat. Remember to do appropriate exercise every day to burn some fast and maintain a good body shape.

The Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) is the amount of heat the body consumes at rest.The higher the BMR, the more calories you burn, and the less likely you are to get fat.

The BMR of normal person is relatively constant. General，the male has a slightly higher BMR than female, and children and youth has a higher BMR than the adult. BMR decreases gradually after adulthood.BMR has a very big impact on weight loss, and daily moderate exercise is helpful to improve the BMR.

Your metabolic level is on the high side at present, having reached the level of burning fat while sitting motionless! To maintain a high BMR, you can do concentrated exercise more than twice a week which lasts about one hour each time and go after a walk after each dinner.

At present, you have not reached the standard, and you can get fat when you eat a little bit too much. The most effective way to improve BMR is exercise, so please jog twice at least every week, and take a walk after the meal in order to raise body metabolization and the ability to consume calories.

At present, your metabolic level is too low, having reached the level of getting fat by drinking water. The most effective way to improve your Basal Metabolic Rate is to exercise. Please jog at least twice a week, and be persistent in exercise to improve your metabolism and burn calories.

So far, you\'re up to your standards, and it\'s easy to maintain your weight as long as you don\'t eat more. The most effective way to maintain your Basal Metabolic Rate is to do some low-intensity exercise every day, like walking and jogging. Remember to have a walk after dinner
Bone salt content refers to the content of inorganic salts in the bone. Bone is composed of inorganic salts, organic matrix and bone cells.
Bone salt increases the hardness of the bone, the matrix determines the shape and toughness of the bone, and bone cells play a leading role in metabolism.

Your bone salt content is on the high side, indicating a comparatively healthy living habits. Bone salt content can undergo natural loss as you age, but you can maintain a healthy level as long as you eat a healthy diet and do reasonable exercise.
You have a low bone salt content, which can lead to back pain, hunchback, and easy fracture. Watch out for alcohol, coffee and strong tea, which can speed up the loss of calcium from your bones.

You have a standard bone salt content. Bone salt content does not change significantly in the short term, but can undergo natural loss as you age. You need to eat a healthy diet and do reasonable exercise to maintain a healthy level.
Fat percentage refers to the proportion of fatty tissue in the total weight of body composition. It\'s the best measure of weight

Body fat plays an important role in maintaining temperature, buffering body impact, moistening the skin, and maintaining normal hormone secretion. For adults, excess fat means the person involved are more likely to suffer from many chronic diseases than the average person.

Your fat percentage is in standard limits, but it is about to exceed the criteria. A big greasy meal or sitting still for long periods of time can make your body fat exceed the standard. If you want to maintain a standard fat percentage and keep away from the warning line, please pay attention to your healthy lifestyle.

You have a high fat percentage and may be at risk for obesity-related diseases. Moderate and low intensity exercise for a long time has a good effect of fat reduction; Combine progressive strength training with high-intensity interval training to maintain muscle mass, increase basal metabolic rate, and improve fat burning efficiency. As for diet, you\'d better give priority to food with low fat and rich protein, and combine all sorts of vegetable and fruit to form the dietary structure of low calorie, high nutrition and great satiety.

Note that your body fat levels are already very unhealthy! High body fat percentage not only causes physical corpulence, but also is the main cause of various chronic diseases. Please reduce the intake of foods high in oil and calories. Start exercising by walking every day and try to get back to a healthy level and restore a good figure!

Your body fat level is on the high side, which will greatly increase the risks of coronary heart disease, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, hyperglycemia, fatty liver and other chronic metabolic diseases. Make sure you get the right amount of exercise every day and adjust your diet.

Thin shape and too low body fat level. In the case of adequate protein intake, please increase the intake of some high-sugar and high-calorie foods (such as fruit juice, cheese, animal liver, etc.), to help build a strong body and enhance immunity.

In view of your age, your body fat level is too low. Please be vigilant about whether there exist chronic diseases, such as tumor, glycosuria disease, chronic liver disease, chronic gastrointestinal disease and other diseases that increase consumption or affect absorption. Please go to the hospital for a check-up.

Your body fat level is low, which can lead to fractures when you fall, slow healing of injuries and surgical wounds and neurological symptoms such as insomnia. Keep a certain amount of body fat can prevent burning of tissue protein in your body when you get sick.

You have a standard body fat level. Maintenance of healthy body fat levels can help better body metabolism, protect fragile bones, reduce the risk of fractures, and improve resistance to cold and disease.

The electrode of the bracelet collects the biological current of the human body and analyzes it to obtain data. Therefore, there is a certain requirement for conductivity to achieve the test condition of the electrode conduction.
Sometimes the skin is dry, and the skin may be poorly conductive especially in autumn and winter. You can blow the skin touching the bracelet or use water to moisten it before retesting.

When testing, please maintain a comfortable sitting posture and a smooth state of mind and avoid talking. Wear the bracelet on the left hand, then touch the right index finger and middle finger to the wrist electrode, and press it moderately to make the two electrodes at the bottom of the bracelet in full contact with the skin. Note that contact between the left and right hands should be avoided.

Muscles have the effect of maintaining body temperature and maintaining physical activity and energy production.

The amount of muscle in the body plays an important role in health. Muscle has a higher metabolic rate than fat. Maintaining a certain amount of muscle promotes metabolism and reduces the risk of chronic diseases associated with metabolic disorders, such as dyslipidemia and diabetes.
At present, your muscles are quite sufficient. Please continue to maintain appropriate exercise and reasonable eating habits.

Your muscle rate is low, which can lead to poor motor performance and slow down your basal metabolism. Strength training two to three times a week can stimulate muscle growth. In terms of diet, you should pay attention to the intake of carbohydrate and high-quality protein to promote glycogen recovery and muscle synthesis, ensure adequate time and quality of sleep, and win enough time for muscle repair.

At present, your muscles are in the standard range. Please continue to maintain the appropriate amount of exercise and a reasonable diet. Too little exercise and dieting are the main causes of muscle loss.
Protein percentage refers to the proportion of protein content in the body weight.

Protein is an important component of all cells and tissues in the human body. All the important components of the human body require the involvement of proteins, which are the main raw materials for tissue renewal and repair.
Your protein level is on the high side, indicating a relative sufficient intake of nutrients. Please also pay attention to a balanced diet and eat more high-fiber vegetables.

Your protein levels are low. The most effective way to increase protein levels in your body is through daily dietary supplements. Egg white, milk and beans are excellent sources of protein, which are low in fat and suitable for the meals.

The protein level is high and your current nutritional intake is adequate. But you are a little too thin, indicating faster body metabolism, and difficulty in increase of body tissues. Please continue to maintain your protein intake.

Human body moisture includes blood, lymphatic fluid, extracellular fluid, intracellular fluid and so on. Water has important functions such as conveying nutrients, recovering body wastes and maintaining body temperature. Therefore, proper daily hydration is very important to maintain good health.

The small fluctuation of HRV within 1 to 149 range in a short time is a normal phenomenon.
It is recommended to measure HRV daily and under in similar conditions (such as after getting up, before falling asleep), and to observe the fluctuation range from multiple measurements.
Within the 1 to 149 range the higher the HRV value, the better the nervous system can regulate the cardiovascular system and the healthier the cardiovascular system becomes.
Deep breathing can temporarily increase HRV. Long-term aerobic exercise and intake of omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids (such as fish oil) can also help to improve the long-term average of HRV.

Heart rate variability (HRV) refers to the change of heart rate per minute. It contains the information of neurohumoral factors regulating cardiovascular system, so as to judge the condition and prevention of cardiovascular diseases.

Heart rate variability in normal state ranges from 1 to 149 per minute. In this range, the higher the heart rate variability, the healthier the cardiovascular system. Heart rate variability over 150 is an abnormal condition, which may be a sign of illness. It is suggested that a detailed examination be carried out in the hospital.
Heart rate variability of more than 150 is an abnormal condition, which may be caused by diseases. It is suggested that a detailed examination be carried out in the hospital.

During excercise, your body can change heart rate more effectively. Studies have shown that people with HRV in the upper range of the normal HRV ( 1 to 149) are healthier, live longer and have lower risk of disease.

Heart rate variability naturally decreases with age. Lack of exercise and smoking can also lead to a decrease in heart rate variability. When the heart rate variability is very low, the risk of heart attack increases. If you feel ill, consult your doctor.

Cardiovascular health index is calculated by the Framingham Heart Study of NHLBI. It can be used to assess the state of angiocarpy completely and qualitatively, and judge the probability of the cardiovascular disease in the future 10 years. The higher the Cardiovascular health index is, the healthier the heart will be. The study shows that the high blood pressure, high cholesterol, diabetes, smoking and other diseases are all the dangerous factors that make people suffer from the cardiovascular disease. In addition, the probability of catching cardiovascular disease will be influenced by the gender, age, innate physiological structure of angiocarpy and inherited factors. \10 At the same time, it’s necessary to provide long-term monitoring for the Cardiovascular health index and help the healthy group to keep the Cardiovascular health index above 90 sustainably. Moreover, the health condition of the cardiovascular system can be improved by quitting smoking, exercising and keeping a healthy life style, so as to control the blood pressure, reduce the blood fat and control the obesity.

Heart rate variability (HRV) refers to the change of the successive heartbeat cycle difference. It usually reflects the activity of the autonomic nerves system, and assesses the tension and balance of the cardiac sympathetic nerve and the pneumogastric nerve quantitatively, so as to judge the condition and prevention of the cardiovascular diseases. Therefore, HRV may be a valuable index to prevent the sudden cardiac death and arrhythmia. \10 According to the findings of the clinical research, HRV declines gradually with the increase of age. Meanwhile, the lack of exercises or smoking will cause the decline of HRV, which usually becomes quite big at the rest state under the condition of good and healthy heart.\10 What’s more, HRV will decrease progressively with the increase of heart rate and exercise intensity during the exercise process. After the exercise, HRV will decline under the condition of great mental stress and excessive fatigue.

Heart rate range, can help you for different exercise intensity, showing different heart rate curve. The maximum range of heart rate is estimated by the formula of 220 minus age. As the following parameters

In the range of 90%-100% of the highest heart rate, reaching almost all strength of training, just for a short time. For athletes, anaerobic training exercise can last for 20-30 minutes (5 km race). And for those who are not adequately trained, anaerobic exercise can lead to a very high metabolic stress, usually only for 2-5 minutes.

In the range of 80%-90% of the highest heart rate, this state is considered to be special for athletes or athletic players, but in fact it is helpful for all of you if you want to be faster and stronger. The state is often named as a critical state, because it is more suitable for those who want to further enhance the speed of exercise. These people often mix fat burning status with cardiopulmonary exercise intensity, doing some changes to improve metabolic capability. Endurance will be promoted with the further enhancement of the muscle\'s tolerance to lactic acid.

In the range of 70%-80% of the highest heart rate, it can enhance your ability of tolerance, which means exercising for a long time without fatigue. Cardiopulmonary exercise can significantly improve health, which can increase the density of mitochondria and improve the utilization of fat so that exercise per minute will consume more calories.

In the range of 60%-70% of the highest heart rate, it is low to moderate intensity exercise that burns more calories and fat than the resting state. In this rate, the sporter may start sweating, but exercise intensity has no effect on conversations between sporters.

In the range of 50%-60% of the highest heart rate, belonging to low intensity exercise, it is beneficial to enhance the metabolic and emotional health. Exercise in this range can lower cholesterol, reduce mental stress and improve blood pressure.
In the range of 25%-50% of the highest heart rate, it often means the number of heartbeat per minute under the state of being awake and inactive.
